item.title: Bow
item.dc:creator: @Tribbinator Tribbinator
item.description:
@Tribbinator wrote:

Java Is My Bitch:

Don’t discourage texturing. Textures are a great way of making your model look good, and fit into a game without killing the graphics card. Although, a huge part of the textures is the model, so don’t think that; since there’s textures, you don’t have to add details to the models, because then your models will make people puke.

I wasnt discouraging texturing, its an amazing thing, I was just speaking to my audience (Tubefish), Little confused on your second sentence, maybe its the wording or my grammatical intelligence, Haha

[quote=“Tribbinator, post:19, topic:363304”][quote author=tubefish link=topic=459558.msg3362474#msg3362474 date=1286498111]
Tribbs can i do TV with you and videotape what you do for an example of UV thats way i understand it better?
[/quote]

Uv’ing is an extremely complex process in metaseq, my best recommendation is a more advanced modelling program (But highly unneccesary to have just for textures)

While textures may looks nice, if you have a good looking model with a flat color on it, that means it is really a good model, because no textures are there to cover up flaws![/quote]Don’t discourage texturing. Textures are a great way of making your model look good, and fit into a game without killing the graphics card. Although, a huge part of the textures is the model, so don’t think that; since there’s textures, you don’t have to add details to the models, because then your models will make people puke.
